My favorite college bar in campus town, Es Tas wins by a long shot with their Taco Tuesday specials.  However, visiting on Tuesday can be uncomfortable because the place will stay crowded for the entire night due to the insanely low prices on just about everything.  People purchase whole pitchers of beers individually and drink for quite a while.  Finding a spot to just sit and enjoy your dinner can become very difficult despite a reasonably large dining area.  As for the tacos themselves, it's special too... two words: DEEP FRIED.  Yeah, I know typical crunchy taco shells are deep fried, but Es Tas freshly deep fried flour tortillas make all the difference in the world.  Pair those $1ish tacos with a basket of tots and a pitcher of fresh tap beer, it's no wonder I'm always at Es Tas on Tuesday nights.  A fine point that may not be appreciated by most, but Es Tas does frequently rotate their tap beers as well.  Given that Märzen is my beer of choice, I frequent Es Tas in the month of October even more than the typical Tuesday visit.
